			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in NetworkManager. When a system running NetworkManager with DEBUG logs enabled and an interface eth1 configured with LLDP enabled, a malicious user could inject a malformed LLDP packet. NetworkManager would crash, leading to a denial of service. \n            STATEMENT: The impact is set to Low as it is very unlikely to have a production system running NetworkManager with DEBUG logs enabled.",
